The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric stove and the hearth. Enclose the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it down. Build a custom closet.
We always start with a quick sketch in pencil...
The dirty phase is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried up :(
Ready for plastering next week
Pleased with the small niche on the side
Insert the new wardrobe here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator !
And we even thought about adding a lovely little ventilation hole to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney sweep took care of installing the hat and the vent. It should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll install the floor tomorrow !
The cork underlayment is laid, I improvised a wood shavings extractor with a toilet paper roll as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Part of the planks are sorted and ready to be laid. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress has been slow today due to very delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the corridor (which is also being laid). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on the knees! Cherry on top: the unpalatable instructions to assemble the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
Still to do: the corridor floor and all the baseboards. The decorator comes in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's the chic of plaster without any finishing touches
Evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with the tenon saw or the chisel where we want the floor to be perfectly fitted.
The cork underlayment of the corridor is also laid
We finished the corridor floor yesterday! Then departure at 5 a.m. this morning to pick up Thing 1 at Heathrow, then a nap and the final stretch for the corridor; baseboards laid. We'll take care of the sealing when the glue has dried.
